4. Grandmaster-Level Modeling (TabPFN + CatBoost)

TabPFN: We integrated a state-of-the-art Tabular Transformer pre-trained on millions of synthetic datasets. It is the current "gold standard" for datasets under 1,000 rows.

CatBoost: We used CatBoost for the Expert segments because its "Ordered Boosting" mechanism is the most resistant to noise in sparse data.

5. Rank Blending (The AUC Cheat Code)

Instead of averaging the probability numbers (e.g., 0.8 + 0.2 = 0.5), we averaged the Ranks (e.g., "Fire A is the 1st most dangerous" + "Fire A is the 3rd most dangerous").

Why it worked: AUC (the metric) only cares about the Order of the fires. Rank blending removes "calibration noise" and focuses 100% on getting the sequence of danger right.

